  "title": "Cardiac Technologist - Central",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provides haemodynamics monitoring support for coronary angiography, angioplasty, and other interventional radiological procedures.</li>\n  <li>Performs Electrophysiology (EPS) studies in collaboration with cardiologists.</li>\n  <li>Assists in post-catheterisation care of patients.</li>\n  <li>Assists in code blue procedures in the cardiovascular laboratory.</li>\n  <li>Performs ECGs, newborn hearing screenings, and other non-radiation procedures in the Diagnostic Imaging Department (DID)/Cardio-Vascular Laboratory (CVL).</li>\n  <li>Assists in portering, preparing, and positioning patients for procedures.</li>\n  <li>Provides administrative support within the DID and CVL departments.</li>\n  <li>Provides on-call coverage for emergency CVL procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Science (Biology/Physiology) or Diploma in Medical Technology (Cardiac Technology) / Biotechnology / Cardiovascular Technology or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Electrophysiology (EPS) studies.</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 2 years of clinical experience in an acute hospital setting.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Haemodynamics monitoring within an invasive laboratory.</li>\n  <li>5.5-day work week (42 hours per week).</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>AHPC registered.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
